To show notices or alerts in the view, you can use Rails' built-in flash messages system. Here's how you can implement it:

1. In your controller actions, set flash messages like this:
   ```ruby
   flash[:notice] = "This is a notice message"
   flash[:alert] = "This is an alert message"
   ```

2. In your layout file (usually app/views/layouts/application.html.erb), add this code where you want the messages to appear:
   ```erb
   <% flash.each do |type, message| %>
     <div class="flash <%= type %>">
       <%= message %>
     </div>
   <% end %>
   ```

3. Style the flash messages in your CSS to make them visually distinct:
   ```css
   .flash {
     padding: 10px;
     margin-bottom: 10px;
     border-radius: 4px;
   }
   .flash.notice {
     background-color: #dff0d8;
     color: #3c763d;
   }
   .flash.alert {
     background-color: #f2dede;
     color: #a94442;
   }
   ```

This approach will display any flash messages set in your controllers, and you can easily customize the appearance to fit your application's design.

