Regarding access to the file name being uploaded, typically you can access this information through the File API in JavaScript. If you're using a file input element, you can get the file name like this:

```javascript
const fileInput = document.querySelector('input[type="file"]');
fileInput.addEventListener('change', (event) => {
  const fileName = event.target.files[0].name;
  console.log('File name:', fileName);
});
```

This code assumes you have a file input in your HTML. It adds an event listener to the file input, and when a file is selected, it logs the name of the first file (in case of multiple file selection).

If you need more specific information about file handling in this particular codebase, you might want to look for other relevant parts of the code, especially those dealing with form submission or file input handling.
